18
00:00:12,332 --> 00:00:15,332
http://hiqve.com/

19
00:00:18,356 --> 00:00:20,107
<i>A last gasp of hope!</i>

20
00:00:20,441 --> 00:00:23,277
<i>After the assassination of his father
and the fall of his kingdom</i>

21
00:00:23,361 --> 00:00:25,655
<i>beneath a planetary civil war,</i>

22
00:00:25,821 --> 00:00:30,034
<i>Mon Cala Prince Lee-Char has gone
into hiding with Padawan Ahsoka Tano</i>

23
00:00:30,117 --> 00:00:31,786
<i>as his only protector.</i>

24
00:00:32,078 --> 00:00:34,288
<i>With his armies captured
and friends imprisoned,</i>

25
00:00:34,330 --> 00:00:37,250
<i>the situation seems hopeless for the prince.</i>

26
00:00:37,500 --> 00:00:40,670
<i>Count Dooku commands
his sinister agent Riff Tamson</i>

27
00:00:40,753 --> 00:00:44,632
<i>to use any means necessary
to bring Prince Lee-Char out of hiding,</i>

28
00:00:44,715 --> 00:00:48,803
<i>for he knows that hope does remain
as long as the prince is alive.</i>

29
00:01:10,283 --> 00:01:14,203
A senator, two Jedi Knights,
and a fumbling amphibian.

30
00:01:14,662 --> 00:01:17,081
I would have thought the prince
would be easier to capture

31
00:01:17,164 --> 00:01:18,749
than the four of you.

32
00:01:18,833 --> 00:01:20,960
It must be part of our plan.

33
00:01:21,085 --> 00:01:23,546
I had the exact same thought.

34
00:01:26,966 --> 00:01:29,260
-Don't touch me.
-Let go of her.

35
00:01:31,721 --> 00:01:34,140
Rack 'em up!

36
00:01:37,935 --> 00:01:38,978
No!

37
00:01:46,193 --> 00:01:49,447
Mesa don't like this. Ow! That pinching!

38
00:01:50,281 --> 00:01:52,074
Tamson, leave them alone.

39
00:01:53,159 --> 00:01:57,538
Do not worry, Jedi,
there's plenty of suffering to go around.

40
00:01:57,872 --> 00:02:00,625
Ah.

41
00:02:00,708 --> 00:02:02,543
Eels, very dangerous.

42
00:02:07,632 --> 00:02:12,261
Now, tell me, where is Prince Lee-Char?

43
00:02:40,456 --> 00:02:42,208
We can't hide forever.

44
00:02:42,249 --> 00:02:45,628
The Gungan Army was the last
of the Republic's reinforcements.

45
00:02:45,961 --> 00:02:47,588
There won't be any more.

46
00:02:47,672 --> 00:02:49,632
The failure is mine, not the Republic's.

47
00:02:49,757 --> 00:02:51,008
Get back!

48
00:03:03,813 --> 00:03:07,525
If my father were here, he could unite
with Nossor Ri and the Quarren.

49
00:03:08,317 --> 00:03:11,779
The Quarren and Mon Cala
have always had a difficult relationship,

50
00:03:11,821 --> 00:03:14,949
but it was respectful,
until Riff Tamson arrived.

51
00:03:15,866 --> 00:03:18,619
Once that Carcadon
got inside Nossor Ri's head

52
00:03:18,828 --> 00:03:22,623
the alliance between the Mon Cala
and the Quarren fell apart.

53
00:03:26,627 --> 00:03:28,170
I know what I must do.

54
00:03:28,254 --> 00:03:31,424
The Mon Cala and Quarren people
must be reunited.

55
00:03:34,760 --> 00:03:38,389
Okay. I like your thinking,
but what's the strategy?

56
00:03:38,764 --> 00:03:42,226
Count all the prisoners,
Mon Cala, Gungans, clones.

57
00:03:42,309 --> 00:03:45,896
If we all fought together
we would outnumber our opponent.

58
00:03:45,980 --> 00:03:49,692
If this is going to work,
we'll need to let your people know.

59
00:03:49,775 --> 00:03:51,485
They'll have to be ready to fight.

60
00:03:51,861 --> 00:03:55,489
We need Captain Ackbar
and I think I know where to find him.

61
00:04:15,509 --> 00:04:18,179
I have interrogated the Jedi, My Lord,

62
00:04:18,429 --> 00:04:21,348
but they will not give up
the whereabouts of the prince.

63
00:04:21,390 --> 00:04:25,060
The Jedi's resistance to pain is impressive.

64
00:04:25,978 --> 00:04:30,524
<i>Press the interrogation, Tamson.
We cannot allow the prince to survive.</i>

65
00:04:31,400 --> 00:04:33,903
<i>The royal bloodline must be broken.</i>

66
00:04:34,403 --> 00:04:37,615
Count Dooku, is this necessary?
The battle is won.

67
00:04:38,157 --> 00:04:40,242
The prince has no army to rally.

68
00:04:40,326 --> 00:04:42,495
Now is the time for the Quarren
to take the lead

69
00:04:42,536 --> 00:04:45,456
-and think of rebuilding.
<i>-Rebuild?</i>

70
00:04:46,457 --> 00:04:50,961
<i>While this battle has been won,
there is still a war going on, Senator Ri.</i>

71
00:04:51,712 --> 00:04:55,883
<i>A war in which you pledged your allegiance
to the Separatist cause!</i>

72
00:04:56,425 --> 00:04:59,512
Of course, Count, we owe you everything.

73
00:05:00,429 --> 00:05:02,556
<i>Do not soon forget it.</i>

74
00:05:03,599 --> 00:05:05,518
<i>Tamson, have your soldiers arrived?</i>

75
00:05:05,893 --> 00:05:08,062
-Soldiers?
-Yes, Count.

76
00:05:09,730 --> 00:05:12,399
We now have the city under our control.

77
00:05:14,235 --> 00:05:17,279
<i>Good. Continue as planned.</i>

78
00:05:43,222 --> 00:05:44,431
It's a prison camp.

79
00:05:44,557 --> 00:05:47,184
How can we be sure
Captain Ackbar is inside?

80
00:05:47,268 --> 00:05:49,645
There's only one way to find out.

81
00:06:18,966 --> 00:06:23,554
Will we ever get out of here?
The city is fallen, prince is lost.

82
00:06:28,392 --> 00:06:29,977
Prince Lee-Char?

83
00:06:31,186 --> 00:06:33,355
Are you a prisoner here as well?

84
00:06:33,439 --> 00:06:37,067
I am here, but not as a prisoner.
I've come with a message.

85
00:06:37,151 --> 00:06:39,945
As your future king, I have not lost hope.

86
00:06:40,154 --> 00:06:42,656
The time is coming when
you will be free again.

87
00:06:42,698 --> 00:06:43,991
I will not fail you.

88
00:06:44,325 --> 00:06:47,328
We want to believe,
but how can this be possible?

89
00:06:47,703 --> 00:06:50,831
-Commander Tano.
-Monnk, am I glad to see you.

90
00:06:51,332 --> 00:06:54,168
Yes, Commander, but you both
must come with me now.

91
00:06:54,251 --> 00:06:56,086
You'll attract too much attention here,

92
00:06:56,170 --> 00:06:59,632
and I think there's someone
who'll be happy to see you.

93
00:06:59,882 --> 00:07:02,217
Prince! You can't leave us here.

94
00:07:04,470 --> 00:07:05,846
Have courage.

95
00:07:05,930 --> 00:07:09,683
The next time I appear to you,
I will appear as your king.

96
00:07:22,863 --> 00:07:25,574
I grow tired of waiting, Jedi.

97
00:07:25,991 --> 00:07:29,870
-Where is the prince?
-Even if we knew, we would not say.

98
00:07:32,414 --> 00:07:33,832
Unfortunate.

99
00:07:39,880 --> 00:07:44,385
To be honest, it matters little to me.
I would torture you either way,

100
00:07:44,718 --> 00:07:47,680
but Count Dooku
insists I capture the prince.

101
00:07:48,013 --> 00:07:52,142
And there is the slight chance
you're deceiving me

102
00:07:52,559 --> 00:07:55,562
and holding back some information
I could use.

103
00:07:55,771 --> 00:07:59,525
And in my position,
I cannot afford to take chance!

104
00:08:02,069 --> 00:08:03,153
No!

105
00:08:06,448 --> 00:08:11,662
Time is of the essence.
Now tell me what I want to know.

106
00:08:30,264 --> 00:08:32,891
You're alive. Captain, you were right.

107
00:08:34,518 --> 00:08:37,438
Prince, I knew you would survive the battle.

108
00:08:37,604 --> 00:08:42,192
Captain, I need your help. I have a plan.
I know how we can win this fight.

109
00:08:42,401 --> 00:08:46,739
But the battle is over, young Prince.
And it appears that we have lost.

110
00:08:46,864 --> 00:08:49,867
No. In truth, we now outnumber our enemy.

111
00:08:50,200 --> 00:08:51,285
We can overwhelm them.

112
00:08:51,326 --> 00:08:55,080
But we are prisoners.
If we revolted thousands would die.

113
00:08:55,456 --> 00:08:58,834
Not if the Quarren struck first
and aided in our attack.

114
00:08:58,917 --> 00:09:01,128
Prince, how can you say this?

115
00:09:01,211 --> 00:09:05,257
The Quarren betrayed us.
They assassinated your father!

116
00:09:05,299 --> 00:09:08,469
No, Captain,
Riff Tamson murdered my father.

117
00:09:08,594 --> 00:09:10,304
Of that, I am sure.

118
00:09:10,679 --> 00:09:13,766
The Quarren are being used,
I've seen it happen before.

119
00:09:13,807 --> 00:09:15,642
Count Dooku has deceived them.

120
00:09:17,644 --> 00:09:18,645
The prince is right.

121
00:09:19,813 --> 00:09:21,398
<i>Riff Tamson murdered my father.</i>

122
00:09:23,942 --> 00:09:25,360
We'll find Nossor Ri.

123
00:09:25,444 --> 00:09:28,322
He was my father's friend.
I know he will listen.

124
00:09:28,447 --> 00:09:33,494
-How can you be certain of this?
-I can't, but it's time for me to lead.

125
00:09:33,994 --> 00:09:36,705
And this, I feel, is my only course of action.

126
00:09:36,789 --> 00:09:40,501
-I will ready our people, Prince.
-But, Captain, you're injured.

127
00:09:40,584 --> 00:09:44,505
I'll be ready to fight with our future king.

128
00:09:45,297 --> 00:09:47,800
I'll marshal the remaining
clones and Gungans.

129
00:09:47,841 --> 00:09:49,176
What will your signal be?

130
00:09:49,259 --> 00:09:52,638
When a Quarren attacks our enemy,
that will be your sign.

131
00:09:58,393 --> 00:09:59,812
You are under arrest.

132
00:10:04,233 --> 00:10:06,527
No, stay your blade, my friend.

133
00:10:07,236 --> 00:10:10,364
I am Lee-Char,
leader of the Mon Cala people,

134
00:10:10,447 --> 00:10:13,408
and I demand to speak to your superiors.

135
00:10:30,134 --> 00:10:32,678
Your friend's time is running short.

136
00:10:32,970 --> 00:10:36,140
I'm beginning to believe you're both telling
the truth, and know nothing about

137
00:10:36,223 --> 00:10:37,975
the prince's whereabouts.

138
00:10:38,976 --> 00:10:41,520
- Yes.
<i>- We have located the prince</i>

139
00:10:41,895 --> 00:10:43,522
<i>and have him in custody.</i>

140
00:10:43,564 --> 00:10:46,817
<i>He has requested an audience
with the leadership.</i>

141
00:10:47,109 --> 00:10:51,238
By all means, bring him to me.
I shall meet you in the throne room.

142
00:10:51,613 --> 00:10:53,073
<i>Roger, roger.</i>

143
00:10:54,199 --> 00:10:55,284
The throne room?

144
00:10:57,536 --> 00:10:58,620
Yes.

145
00:10:59,121 --> 00:11:04,334
I want that little one to see me
in my rightful place as ruler of this world.

146
00:11:05,252 --> 00:11:09,381
Ruler? That was not our arrangement
with Count Dooku.

147
00:11:10,465 --> 00:11:15,095
No, it wasn't your arrangement.
It was mine!

148
00:11:17,347 --> 00:11:20,267
Wait! The prisoner! You have to save her!

149
00:11:23,562 --> 00:11:26,773
-No, I don't.
-Tamson...

150
00:11:34,740 --> 00:11:36,825
Ani, mesa have an idea.

151
00:11:37,284 --> 00:11:39,786
Not now, Jar Jar. We need to save Padmé.

152
00:11:41,246 --> 00:11:44,124
Anakin, we must create a bubble
for her to breathe from.

153
00:11:44,166 --> 00:11:46,793
Use the Force to push the water
away from her helmet.

154
00:11:46,835 --> 00:11:48,170
I'm on it.

155
00:11:53,592 --> 00:11:55,677
It's working ! It's working!

156
00:11:58,305 --> 00:11:59,306
Look out!

157
00:12:04,603 --> 00:12:05,646
Jar Jar?

158
00:12:06,521 --> 00:12:09,316
-Padmé! I'm sorry I couldn't...
-I'm here.

159
00:12:09,775 --> 00:12:12,236
Jar Jar sealed my helmet with his...

160
00:12:12,319 --> 00:12:17,157
Yesa. It's Gungan waterproofing.
It's why wesa swim so good.

161
00:12:32,214 --> 00:12:33,840
Greetings, Prince.

162
00:12:36,051 --> 00:12:37,552
We meet again.

163
00:12:39,346 --> 00:12:42,975
I must admit you were more
difficult to capture

164
00:12:43,016 --> 00:12:45,018
than I anticipated, Prince.

165
00:12:45,102 --> 00:12:48,397
You have my respect as hunter to his prey.

166
00:12:49,189 --> 00:12:52,025
I do not seek, nor do I want your respect.

167
00:12:52,359 --> 00:12:54,861
I have come to demand
the freedom of my people.

168
00:12:56,363 --> 00:12:57,739
Your people?

169
00:12:58,365 --> 00:13:02,786
You're mistaken, Prince.
They are my people and under my rule.

170
00:13:03,495 --> 00:13:07,749
They, like you,
are nothing more than slaves.

171
00:13:08,583 --> 00:13:11,378
Your rule is not recognized here, Tamson.

172
00:13:11,420 --> 00:13:13,755
My people are all those
who live in these seas,

173
00:13:13,839 --> 00:13:16,383
whether they be Mon Cala or Quarren.

174
00:13:18,719 --> 00:13:22,806
Surely you have not come here
seeking the aid of Nossor Ri.

175
00:13:23,724 --> 00:13:27,352
Do you really think he would trade
his position to join you?

176
00:13:27,394 --> 00:13:30,772
The Quarren are already slaves,
though they may not see it.

177
00:13:31,064 --> 00:13:33,275
Nossor Ri, you knew my father.

178
00:13:33,525 --> 00:13:36,111
Whatever differences
our people had in the past,

179
00:13:36,194 --> 00:13:39,823
surely you must know we can work
together to make Mon Cala whole.

180
00:13:40,407 --> 00:13:42,951
Dooku and Tamson want only to exploit us,

181
00:13:43,035 --> 00:13:45,829
and leave our cities broken
and our resources depleted.

182
00:13:46,663 --> 00:13:49,082
What will then be left for the Quarren?

183
00:13:49,166 --> 00:13:56,089
Well, Nossor Ri, would you like to join
this pitiful little fish and his dead father?

184
00:13:57,507 --> 00:13:59,968
There, you see.

185
00:14:00,052 --> 00:14:02,804
What good will
their help be anyway, Prince?

186
00:14:02,888 --> 00:14:05,891
The Quarren are more gutless
than your people.

187
00:14:06,308 --> 00:14:07,601
As long as I live,

188
00:14:07,684 --> 00:14:11,271
I shall give all people of Mon Cala
hope to fight another day.

189
00:14:11,313 --> 00:14:12,397
Hmm.

190
00:14:12,439 --> 00:14:16,109
Hope? We are of the same mind, Prince.

191
00:14:16,610 --> 00:14:19,863
That is why I have scheduled
your public execution.

192
00:14:20,113 --> 00:14:21,573
Take him away!

193
00:14:21,782 --> 00:14:26,328
Nossor Ri, there's still time!
Unite and we will defend our home.

194
00:14:40,675 --> 00:14:42,928
All right, I think I'm getting the hang of this.

195
00:14:45,347 --> 00:14:47,099
Less talking helps.

196
00:15:00,821 --> 00:15:04,699
Jar Jar, I can't see anything.
Where are they taking us?

197
00:15:04,783 --> 00:15:07,702
Hey, yo us a. Where yo us a taking us?

198
00:15:07,786 --> 00:15:10,664
To the execution of Prince Lee-Char.

199
00:15:40,360 --> 00:15:42,237
Good job protecting the prince.

200
00:15:42,821 --> 00:15:44,739
It's all part of the plan, Master.

201
00:15:45,073 --> 00:15:48,201
I was hoping you were going to say that.
Anything I can do?

202
00:15:48,285 --> 00:15:51,204
Unfortunately, this time
it's out of our hands.

203
00:15:51,288 --> 00:15:54,040
I'm not sure I like this plan after all.

204
00:15:55,375 --> 00:15:58,628
For crimes against the Separatist state,

205
00:15:58,920 --> 00:16:04,801
I command the execution
of former Prince Lee-Char.

206
00:16:09,556 --> 00:16:14,060
Captain, Nossor Ri and the Quarren
are with you.

207
00:16:22,152 --> 00:16:23,278
Kill him!

208
00:16:34,748 --> 00:16:38,585
Fight, Quarren ! Fight for Prince Lee-Char!

209
00:17:10,784 --> 00:17:13,286
-Send in more droids!
-Roger, roger.

210
00:18:55,889 --> 00:18:57,182
Look out!

211
00:19:19,871 --> 00:19:21,748
Prince Lee-Char.

212
00:19:22,415 --> 00:19:25,085
Your rule is at an end
before it started, Tamson!

213
00:19:35,011 --> 00:19:40,058
I killed your father
without pity or mercy.

214
00:19:40,433 --> 00:19:42,060
Then I'll return the favor!

215
00:20:08,628 --> 00:20:10,213
The day is won!

216
00:20:11,256 --> 00:20:13,049
Long live the prince!

217
00:20:13,133 --> 00:20:18,638
Long live the prince!
Long live the prince! Long live the prince!

218
00:20:40,034 --> 00:20:42,287
Your father would be so proud.

219
00:20:42,829 --> 00:20:44,038
I know.

220
00:20:44,831 --> 00:20:47,709
May the blessings of the water keep you.

221
00:20:49,210 --> 00:20:52,839
The might of your ancestors,
give you strength.

222
00:20:58,261 --> 00:21:03,850
As representative of the Quarren people,
I pledge our loyalty to you.

223
00:21:05,351 --> 00:21:10,231
And as your king, I pledge my loyalty
to all people of Mon Cala.

224
00:21:17,113 --> 00:21:21,701
I present King Lee-Char!

225
00:21:21,743 --> 00:21:25,497
Long live the king !
Long live King Lee-Char!

226
00:21:26,247 --> 00:21:29,918
Long live the king ! Long live King Lee-Char!

227
00:21:29,942 --> 00:21:34,942
http://hiqve.com/

